ree_1            = \n| free_label_2      = \n| free_2            = \n| free_label_3      = \n| free_3            = \n| test_name         = \n| test_average      = \n| national_ranking  = \n| website           = [http://www.eganschool.org eganschool.org]\n| footnotes         = \n| picture           = \n| picture_caption   = \n| picture2          = \n| picture_caption2  = \n|superintendent = Jeff Baier}}\n'''Ardis G. Egan Junior High School''' is a [[middle school]] for seventh graders and eighth graders in [[Los Altos, California]]. It is part of  the [[Los Altos School District]]. Most of Egan's over five hundred students live in [[Los Altos, California|Los Altos]] and [[Los Altos Hills]], and a few students live in [[Mountain View, California|Mountain View]].<ref>[http://www.losaltos.k12.ca.us/PDF_Files/Boundaries_2003.pdf Los Altos Elementary Attendance Areas], accessed January 2, 2007</ref> Egan is named after Ardis Egan, the founder and former Superintendent of the Los Altos School District.<ref>[http://www.eganschool.org/egan2/about_egan/about_egan.html Overview of Egan Junior High \u2014 Home of the Vikings], accessed January 2, 2007</ref>\n\nEgan is mainly fed by local [[elementary schools]] of the [[Los Altos School District#Elementary schools (K-6)|same district]]: Almond, Santa Rita, Covington and Gardner Bullis. Egan has inherited these schools' high success rates, ranking as one of the top [[intermediate schools]] in the [[California|state]].\n\n==Awards and recognition==\nIn 1988, 1990, and 2009, Egan was chosen as a [[California Distinguished School]],<ref>{{cite web|title=California Distinguished Schools Awardees 2009|url=https://www.cde.ca.gov/ta/sr/cs/disting2009.asp|website=California Distinguished Schools Awardees|publisher=California Department of Education|accessdate=5 March 2018}}</ref><ref>Cal. Dept. of Education[http://www.cde.ca.gov/ta/sr/cs/ap/distingcounty.asp?county=43&submit1=Submit \"Distinguished School Awards: Award Winners for Santa Clara County,\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070311125323/http://www.cde.ca.gov/ta/sr/cs/ap/distingcounty.asp?county=43&submit1=Submit |date=March 11, 2007 }} accessed December 1, 2006.</ref> and it has often scored high in [[Standardized Testing and Reporting|STAR]] testing. It has been reported as the public school with the highest STAR test scores in California numerous times.<ref>[http://www.latc.com/2001/10/24/schools/schools3.html LASD tops in test scores for third year in a row], ''Los Altos Town Crier'', October 24, 2001 {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060624060124/http://www.latc.com/2001/10/24/schools/schools3.html |date=2006-06-24 }}</ref> From 1999 to 2002, Egan was ranked as the top junior high school in the state, based on its performance on the Academic Performance Index (API) Growth Reports.<ref>Sara Ballenger, [http://www.latc.com/2002/10/29/schools/news01.html Egan named No. 1 jr. high school in state for third year in a row] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927173303/http://www.latc.com/2002/10/29/schools/news01.html |date=2007-09-27 }}, ''Los Altos Town Crier''We are very well known and high in academics., October 30, 2002{{dl|date=March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Education==\nGreatschools awarded Egan a 9/10 in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.greatschools.net/school/rating.page?id=5517&state=CA#from..Tab|title=Egan Junior High School, Los Altos, California|publisher=Great Schools|accessdate=2018-03-04}}</ref>\n\nEgan is one of the few schools in the [[Bay Area]] that offers two Spanish classes: the regular Spanish 1A class and a Spanish Conversation class.{{cn|date=March 2018}} Like all schools in the [[Los Altos School District]], Egan has a musical program. Their [[Band (music)|band]], [[orchestra]], and [[choir|chorus]] visit [[Disneyland]] every year to perform at a concert ([[Magic Music Days]]).<ref>[http://www.eganschool.org/egan2/activities_events/disneyland_trip.html Disney Land Trip], accessed January 22, 2007 {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090307154557/http://www.eganschool.org/egan2/activities_events/disneyland_trip.html |date=2009-03-07 }}</ref>\n\nEgan is well funded with a variety of electives, including [[Technology]], [[Music]], Languages, and Miscellaneous Items, such as [[Art]], [[Yearbook]], [[Economics|Financial Wisdom]], and [[Leadership]]. It also offers a variety of classes that allow students to learn teaching, secretary skills, and librarian skills. Besides, it has many well-funded main courses, [[Algebra]], [[Science]], [[History]], [[English studies|English]], and [[Physical Education]]. [[Los Altos, California|Los Altos]]'s wealthy environment helps Egan's education funding.\n\nEgan has sports programs for boys and girls in [[soccer]], [[basketball]], [[tennis]], [[track and field]], [[Cross country running|cross-country]], [[volleyball]], [[scholastic wrestling|wrestling]], [[American football|football]], and others. Egan students also compete in the national [[MathCounts]] and AMC8 Math competitions. Egan students also compete in the national Science Olympiade competition.\n\nStudents are given awards for a variety of achievements; the most notable of these awards is the \"Block E\", which is earned through sports, after-school activities, and service to the school.<ref>[http://www.eganschool.org/egan2/policy_docs/eganhandbook.html#student_awards Viking Pin, Block E and Star Awards], accessed January 2, 2007</ref>\n\n==Miscellaneous==\n[[Bullis Charter School]] (BCS) also has its campus on the east side of Egan's grounds bordering San Antonio Road. The [[Los Altos School District]] (LASD) offered to let BCS use this space (known at the time as the Egan camp school) from 1 May 2004.<ref>http://www.losaltosonline.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=12310&Itemid=56</ref> The charter school has been located here ever since.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.egan.losaltos.k12.ca.us/ Egan School home page]\n* [http://www.greatschools.net/modperl/browse_school/ca/5517/ Egan School Reviews]\n\n{{LASD}}\n{{Los Altos, California}}\n\n[[Category:Public middle schools in California]]\n[[Category:Los Altos, California]]\n[[Category:Schools in Santa Clara County, California]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox school\n| name              = Ardis G. Egan Intermediate School\n| native_name       = \n| image             = \n| image_size        = \n| alt               = \n| caption           = \n| logo              = \n| motto             = \n| established       = \n| closed            = \n| type              = Public\n| status            = \n| category_label    = \n| category          = \n| gender_label      = \n| gender            = \n| affiliation       = \n| affiliations      = \n| administrator     = \n| assst_admin       = \n| president         = \n| chairman_label    = \n| chairman          = \n| rector            = \n| principal         = Keith Rocha\n| asst principal    = \n| campus_director   = \n| headmaster        = \n| head_name         = Second Master\n| head              = \n| head_name2        = Assistant Headmaster\n| head2             = \n| dean              = \n| founder           = \n| chaplain          = \n| officer_in_charge = \n| faculty           = \n| teaching_staff    = \n| enrollment        = \n| grades_label      = \n| grades            = 7-8\n| streetaddress     =100 W Portola Ave \n| city              = [[Los Altos, California|Los Altos]]\n| state             = [[California]]\n| province          = \n| country           = [[United States|U.S.]]\n| coordinates       = {{Coord|37|23|46|N|122|07|00|W|format=dms|display=inline,title|type:edu_region:US-CA}}\n| latitude          = \n| longitude         = \n| district          =Los Altos School District \n| oversight         = \n| accreditation     = \n| campus            = \n| colors            = [[Blue]] and [[Gold (color)|Gold]]\n| colours           = \n| athletics         = \n| houses            = \n| student_union     = \n| nickname          = \n| mascot            = [[Viking]]\n| free_label        = [[Emblem]]\n| free_text         = \n| rival             = \n| yearbook          = \n| newspaper          = \n| free_label_1      = \n| free_1            = \n| free_label_2      = \n| free_2            = \n| free_label_3      = \n| free_3            = \n| test_name         = \n| test_average      = \n| national_ranking  = \n| website           = [http://www.eganschool.org eganschool.org]\n| footnotes         = \n| picture           = \n| picture_caption   = \n| picture2          = \n| picture_caption2  = \n|superintendent = Jeff Baier}}\n'''Ardis G. Egan Junior High School''' is a [[middle school]] for seventh graders and eighth graders in [[Los Altos, California]]. It is part of  the [[Los Altos School District]]. Most of Egan's over five hundred students live in [[Los Altos, California|Los Altos]] and [[Los Altos Hills]], and a few students live in [[Mountain View, California|Mountain View]].<ref>[http://www.losaltos.k12.ca.us/PDF_Files/Boundaries_2003.pdf Los Altos Elementary Attendance Areas], accessed January 2, 2007</ref> Egan is named after Ardis Egan, the founder and former Superintendent of the Los Altos School District.<ref>[http://www.eganschool.org/egan2/about_egan/about_egan.html Overview of Egan Junior High \u2014 Home of the Vikings], accessed January 2, 2007</ref>\n\nEgan is mainly fed by local [[elementary schools]] of the [[Los Altos School District#Elementary schools (K-6)|same district]]: Almond, Santa Rita, Covington and Gardner Bullis. Egan has inherited these schools' high success rates, ranking as one of the top [[intermediate schools]] in the [[California|state]].\n\n==Awards and recognition==\nIn 1988, 1990, and 2009, Egan was chosen as a [[California Distinguished School]],<ref>{{cite web|title=California Distinguished Schools Awardees 2009|url=https://www.cde.ca.gov/ta/sr/cs/disting2009.asp|website=California Distinguished Schools Awardees|publisher=California Department of Education|accessdate=5 March 2018}}</ref><ref>Cal. Dept. of Education[http://www.cde.ca.gov/ta/sr/cs/ap/distingcounty.asp?county=43&submit1=Submit \"Distinguished School Awards: Award Winners for Santa Clara County,\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070311125323/http://www.cde.ca.gov/ta/sr/cs/ap/distingcounty.asp?county=43&submit1=Submit |date=March 11, 2007 }} accessed December 1, 2006.</ref> and it has often scored high in [[Standardized Testing and Reporting|STAR]] testing. It has been reported as the public school with the highest STAR test scores in California numerous times.<ref>[http://www.latc.com/2001/10/24/schools/schools3.html LASD tops in test scores for third year in a row], ''Los Altos Town Crier'', October 24, 2001 {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060624060124/http://www.latc.com/2001/10/24/schools/schools3.html |date=2006-06-24 }}</ref> From 1999 to 2002, Egan was ranked as the top junior high school in the state, based on its performance on the Academic Performance Index (API) Growth Reports.<ref>Sara Ballenger, [http://www.latc.com/2002/10/29/schools/news01.html Egan named No. 1 jr. high school in state for third year in a row] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927173303/http://www.latc.com/2002/10/29/schools/news01.html |date=2007-09-27 }}, ''Los Altos Town Crier''We are very well known and high in academics., October 30, 2002{{dl|date=March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Education==\nGreatschools awarded Egan a 9/10 in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.greatschools.net/school/rating.page?id=5517&state=CA#from..Tab|title=Egan Junior High School, Los Altos, California|publisher=Great Schools|accessdate=2018-03-04}}</ref>\n\nEgan is among one of the few schools in the [[Bay Area]] that offers two Spanish classes: the regular Spanish 1A class and a Spanish Conversation class.{{cn|date=March 2018}} Like all schools in the [[Los Altos School District]], Egan has a musical program. Their [[Band (music)|band]], [[orchestra]], and [[choir|chorus]] visit [[Disneyland]] every year to perform at a concert ([[Magic Music Days]]).<ref>[http://www.eganschool.org/egan2/activities_events/disneyland_trip.html Disney Land Trip], accessed January 22, 2007 {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090307154557/http://www.eganschool.org/egan2/activities_events/disneyland_trip.html |date=2009-03-07 }}</ref>\n\nEgan is well funded with a variety of electives, including [[Technology]], [[Music]], Languages, and Miscellaneous Items, such as [[Art]], [[Yearbook]], [[Economics|Financial Wisdom]], and [[Leadership]]. It also offers a variety of classes that allow students to learn teaching, secretary skills, and librarian skills. Besides, it has many well-funded main courses, [[Algebra]], [[Science]], [[History]], [[English studies|English]], and [[Physical Education]]. [[Los Altos, California|Los Altos]]'s wealthy environment helps Egan's education funding.\n\nEgan has sports programs for boys and girls in [[soccer]], [[basketball]], [[tennis]], [[track and field]], [[Cross country running|cross-country]], [[volleyball]], [[scholastic wrestling|wrestling]], [[American football|football]], and others. Egan students also compete in the national [[MathCounts]] and AMC8 Math competitions. Egan students also compete in the national Science Olympiade competition.\n\nStudents are given awards for a variety of achievements; the most notable of these awards is the \"Block E\", which is earned through sports, after-school activities, and service to the school.<ref>[http://www.eganschool.org/egan2/policy_docs/eganhandbook.html#student_awards Viking Pin, Block E and Star Awards], accessed January 2, 2007</ref>\n\n==Miscellaneous==\n[[Bullis Charter School]] (BCS) also has its campus on the east side of Egan's grounds bordering San Antonio Road. The [[Los Altos School District]] (LASD) offered to let BCS use this space (known at the time as the Egan camp school) from 1 May 2004.<ref>http://www.losaltosonline.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=12310&Itemid=56</ref> The charter school has been located here ever since.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.egan.losaltos.k12.ca.us/ Egan School home page]\n* [http://www.greatschools.net/modperl/browse_school/ca/5517/ Egan School Reviews]\n\n{{LASD}}\n{{Los Altos, California}}\n\n[[Category:Public middle schools in California]]\n[[Category:Los Altos, California]]\n[[Category:Schools in Santa Clara County, California]]\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "Reword - you can't be \"among one\"", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Egan_Junior_High_School"}
